{"questionId":"33464126","questionHtml":"<p>Find the coefficient of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>8</mn></msup></math> in the expansion of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>11</mn></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to form a product of binomial coefficient, a power of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></math> and a power of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></math> seen<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>8</mn><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>11</mn></mmultiscripts><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>8</mn></msup><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>3</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>3</mn><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>11</mn></mmultiscripts><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>8</mn></msup><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>3</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>165</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>8</mn></msup><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>3</mn></msup></math>.<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (</strong><strong>A1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>8</mn><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>11</mn></mmultiscripts></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mn>3</mn><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>11</mn></mmultiscripts></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>165</mn></math>, <em><strong>A1&nbsp;</strong></em>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>8</mn></msup><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>3</mn></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use the general term<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>C</mi><mi>r</mi><mprescripts></mprescripts><mrow></mrow><mn>11</mn></mmultiscripts><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>11</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>r</mi></msup></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>5280000</mn></math></strong> (exact)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award <em><strong>A0</strong></em> for a final answer of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>5280000</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>8</mn></msup></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33464126","referenceCode":"24N.2.SL.TZ1.2","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the coefficient of x8 in the expansion of (2x-5)11.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"2","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.9—Binomial theorem where n is an integer"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}